# Licensing Overview

This repository contains two categories of content with different licenses:

1. Documentation (all files under `docs/` unless otherwise noted) is licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International License (CC BY 4.0). See `docs/LICENSE-CC-BY-4.0.md`.
2. Example scripts / configuration snippets (if any added later) are licensed under the GNU General Public License v3.0 (GPL-3.0-or-later) unless an individual file header specifies otherwise. See `docs/LICENSE-GPL-3.0.md`.

Open Journal Systems (OJS) itself is developed and distributed by the Public Knowledge Project (PKP) under the GNU General Public License v3. Refer to: https://pkp.sfu.ca/ojs/

Attribution Requirements:
- Credit "Public Knowledge Project (PKP)" for OJS software.
- Include link to https://pkp.sfu.ca/ and OJS project page.
- Retain original license notices in any redistributed code derived from OJS.

